            705,
            336,
            721
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.03",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            417,
            756,
            555,
            771
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Equity value of company A is  \\(1560 = 40\\%\\)  [3000 + 1000 + 400 - 500]. Equity value of company B is  \\(240 = 12\\%\\)  [1000 + 800 + 200].",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            787,
            822,
            824
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidated equity value is 1800.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            838,
            444,
            855
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 7 CONSOLIDATION QUIZZ",
        "bbox": [
            502,
            73,
            855,
            89
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.04",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            427,
            124,
            567,
            139
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidated reserves before transaction",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            158,
            516,
            175
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "For company A: (400) = 80% * 2000 - 100% * 2000",
            "For company B: (160) = 48% * 1000 - 80% * 800"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            152,
            186,
            730,
            239
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "giving a total of  \\((560) = (400) + (160)\\)",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            253,
            495,
            272
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidated reserves after transaction",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            285,
            500,
            303
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "For company A : (240) = 48% * 2000 - 60% * 2000",
            "For company B: (200) = 60% * 1000 - 100% * 800"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            152,
            316,
            716,
            366
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "giving a total of  \\((440) = (240) + (200)\\)",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            382,
            495,
            401
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The impact on A and B consolidated reserves is  \\(120 = (440) - (560)\\)",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            414,
            779,
            432
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.05",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            427,
            464,
            565,
            480
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Option a: Not correct",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            500,
            326,
            517
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Year 1 closing assets and liabilities will not impact the cash flow statement because they have not been acquired. The only cash out to show is the acquisition price of the shares giving the control on that company.",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            532,
            881,
            583
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Option b: Not correct",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            596,
            328,
            612
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A goodwill never appears in a cash flow statement. A goodwill is only a part of the transaction amount.",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            627,
            879,
            661
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Option c: Not correct",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            677,
            326,
            693
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This amount of 400 corresponding to the acquisition price less the goodwill is also a part of the acquisition price. It doesn't appear in the cash flow statement.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            708,
            879,
            756
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Option d: Correct",
        "bbox": [
            114,
            772,
            290,
            788
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Whatever the consolidation method may be or the percentage acquired, the only amount impacting the cash flow statement is the acquisition price.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            804,
            879,
            838
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            67,
            372,
            83
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.06",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            419,
            122,
            559,
            138
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The first step when deconsolidating a company is to consolidate that company with the equity method.",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            157,
            869,
            191
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The equity value would be  \\(1350 = 50\\%\\)  \\* [2000 + 1000 + (300)].",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            204,
            755,
            223
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The second step consists in modifying the value to bring it to the statutory financial investment of 1800. This can be done by a debit 450 on the equity value and a credit 450 on a profit account. This last booking is the answer.",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            238,
            871,
            286
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.07",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            419,
            320,
            559,
            336
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Equity value of company B = 520 = 20%  \\(\\star\\)  [2000 + 1000 + 200 - 600].",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            368,
            814,
            388
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The indirect group financial percentage in company A is  \\(64\\% = 60\\% + 20\\%\\)  and  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties indirect percentage is  \\(36\\% = 100\\% - 64\\%\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            400,
            869,
            435
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Minority interests are  \\(1980 = 36\\%\\)  \\* [3000 + 2000 + 5001.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            448,
            691,
            467
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.08",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            419,
            502,
            556,
            517
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We first have to evaluate the consolidated equity of the subgroup which is",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            536,
            829,
            554
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "Capital of company  \\(A = 3000\\)",
            "Reserves of company A = 2000",
            "Result of company  \\(A = 1000\\)",
            "- Consolidated reserves of company B = 420 = 70% * [2000 + 500 + 100] - [1500 + (100)]"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            145,
            568,
            869,
            649
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "that is a total of 6420.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            663,
            333,
            679
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Considering a selling price of  \\(X\\) , company  \\(P\\)  would make a profit of  \\(X - 60\\% * 6420 = X - 3852\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            695,
            871,
            729
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "But this profit has to be decreased by the 500 goodwill attached to the  \\(60\\%\\)  shares, which gives a final profit of X - 3852 - 500 that must be equal to 300.",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            744,
            871,
            792
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We find  \\(X = 4652\\)",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            808,
            293,
            824
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 7 CONSOLIDATION QUIZZ",
        "bbox": [
            504,
            74,
            856,
            90
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.09",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            427,
            124,
            567,
            139
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We have seen several times through our different examples that when a company is consolidated with a percentage X until a shareholder decides to sell a percentage of Y, the following part of consolidated reserves, that is \"consolidated reserves * (Y / X)\" are transferred from the concerned company to the shareholder.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            158,
            879,
            238
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In our case, we speak about a ratio of  \\(\\frac{1}{4} = 20\\% / 80\\%\\)  which applies to the remaining consolidated reserves  \\(180 = 200 + (20)\\) . Indeed, dividends paid must be deducted because already transferred (paid) to the shareholder.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            254,
            879,
            304
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The correct answer is (45) = - 180  \\(\\star\\)  (20% / 80%).",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            316,
            616,
            336
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer 3.10",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            427,
            368,
            565,
            383
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's suppose the unknown acquisition price for the  \\(30\\%\\)  is  \\(X\\)  and the resulting goodwill is  \\(G\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            402,
            877,
            437
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We are now able to calculate the consolidated equity used in the ratio, which is",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            450,
            877,
            483
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "Equity of parent company  \\(= 3000\\)",
            "- Consolidated reserves of company  \\(A = 70\\% * 2000 - [1000 + X - G] = 400 - P + X\\)",
            "Minority interests of company A = 600 = 30% * 2000"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            150,
            499,
            875,
            563
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "giving a total of  \\(4000 - X + G\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            579,
            413,
            597
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "But, in order to comply with Bankers requests, we have to reduce the equity by the goodwill. Consolidated equity becomes 4000 - X.",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            612,
            875,
            645
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "After global integration, debts become  \\(4000 = 2000 + 2000\\)  and the ratio \"Debt/Consolidated equity\" is  \\(4000 / [4000 - X] = 2\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            658,
            875,
            693
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We easily find  \\(X = 2000\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            707,
            355,
            724
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
